A teenager was shot dead on his way to school in Port Elizabeth s northern areas yesterday. Renaldo Maarman, 17, was gunned down in Lodewyk Road, Bloemendal, shortly before 8am. By yesterday afternoon, detectives were still unsure if Maarman had been the intended target or had been struck by a stray bullet. He was shot twice in the upper body and died less than 500m from his school. The police gang intervention unit was still on the scene at 1pm. The Bertram High School pupil was on his way to school when he was killed as he was dressed in his uniform, according to police. Police spokeswoman Colonel Priscilla Naidu said detectives were struggling to find witnesses. Details remain sketchy as no one has come forward, she said. Information suggested that an unknown number of people had started shooting at the teenager. It was unknown if he had been linked to a gang or what the motive for the attack had been, Naidu said. For the full story read The Herald/Weekend Post, or get the complete newspaper, including comics, classifieds, crosswords and back editions in our e-Edition. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Related Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share